message.raw:
Fixed bug that prevented transition to manual when no channels acquired.
Also changed acquire definition for labscript file calls. This should more in line with other devices.

Device and Channels are defined in connection table.
Individual channels to be acquired must call acquire() in script.
Device then must call acquire(t) to send trigger.
This allows for configurable channel acquires without changing the connection table.

message.raw:
Added check for NI PCIe 6363 to ensure that the current version of NI-DAQmx is not 14.0.

NI-DAQmx v14.0 seems to have a bug where the Digital Output task raises the following exception: "DAQError: Finite acquisition or generation has been stopped before the requested number of samples were acquired or generated."

Other versions of NI-DAQmx don't seem to have this issue, and neither does the NI PCI 6733 even when using DAQmx v14.0.

The issue is resolved using NI DAQmx v14.2 or higher (also tested as working with v9.2.3)

message.raw:
Restores previous symmetric clock pulses as the default behaviour for the PulseBlaster (fixes #16)

Also fixes issues with:
 * long delay instructions (the number of reps must be at least 2)
 * calculation of when to use a long delay instruction when using assymetric clock pulses
 * assymetric clock pulses don't make sense if it isn't used as a pseudoclock (now raises LabscriptError)

message.raw:
Updated NI PCI 6733 device to add features and fix bugs

 * Added manual control of PFI flags
 * Fixed bugs in BLACS worker process preventing use of digital outputs in experiments
 * Fixed bug in labscript code which demanded an even number of child devices, not an even number of AnalogOuts
 * Fixed bug in labscript code which had the incorrect dtype for the digital output numpy array. This caused an obscure "index out of range" error in a bitfield conversion.

Fixed bug where any device based on PulseBlaster_No_DDS did not get labels on the front panel buttons in BLACS.
This was because the change to the pseudoclock/clockline object hierarchy in labscript requires an extra method to be defined in the tab class as outputs are now more removed from the device the tab belongs to.

fixes #9

  argument and h5 attribute must have the same name, so one of them had to
  change since this was previously inconsistent. Kept backward compatibility
  for now such that exposuretime can still be passed in as a kwarg and things
  will work.

- Fixed incorrect calls to labscript_utils.properties.get() in NI cards

- Moved clock_terminal to be a connection table property of NI cards, rather
  than a device property

- Fixed incorrect call to self.set_property in PhaseMatrixQuickSyn

Bumped version requirements to labscript 2.1, blacs 2.1

message.raw:
Update all device's __init__ method to be decoraited by @set_passed_properties()
in most cases I used @set_passed_properties(keep_names = []) indicating that
none of the kw parameters were to be entered into the properties field.

In the case of the Camera device, all of the information that is currently stored
as attributes to the device is also being stored in this field (since this is
really where it belongs).  The NIST imaging software will pull all camera info
from this connection table field rather than the device attributes.  The device
attributes will currently be left in place for backwards compatability.

attributes to any device.  This involves some effort to pass **kwargs in
__init__ all the way up to the root Device class.  Part of this will/may
have me writing attributes to a new "Config" group in the device group in the
h5 file, so I will also be moving the code which creates the individual
device group into the root __init__ as well.
